Make the dressing. Combine all of the ingredients together in a jar, and shake until blended. Pat the shrimp dry with paper towels, and place in a bowl. Add 2 tbsp of the dressing and toss. Toss the grapefruit, radishes, avocados, scallions, greens, watercress, and mint leaves in a large bowl. Divide among 6 dinner plates. Arrange 5 shrimp on top of each, and drizzle with the remaining dressing. Serve immediately. Variation: Lobster and Crab Salad: Substitute chunks of lobster or lump crab meat for the shrimp. Lobster and Crab Salad: Substitute chunks of lobster or lump crab meat for the shrimp.